# Summary
[beyond_mode_only]
[early_info]

Switches camera to follow player.

# Input Parameters
* [input:Player_Entity] (Entity) - Entity of the player to switch the camera for.

# Usage
Starting in Luna VI, craftsperson can configure the camera to follow an entity.
This allows finer control over the position of the camera and its movement.
After using [node:set_player_camera_to_follow_entity],
this node can be used to come back to the player camera.

# Example
In this example, we reset the camera to the player camera for the player that selects the tab.
[image:reset_player_camera_to_follow_entity_example]

# Notes
* If [input:Player_Entity] is not a player entity,
  this node raises "Entity does not exist" error
  (can be misleading, because the entity may exist)
  but continues the execution.
* If you switch from the default camera A to a player camera B and then to an object camera C,
  using this node will switch the camera back to camera B, not camera A.

# Performance
This node took ~8 units to run on average.

